author: National Geographic
description:
Black Voyage follows Brooklyn-based photographer and creative director Lougè Delcy as he returns to Kenya to reconnect with the Maasai—a journey inspired by his first visit to Africa in 2018. As he prepares for his first solo exhibition, he immerses himself in Maasai life, capturing their strength, traditions, and spirit through his lens. This episode is a powerful exploration of rediscovery, cultural immersion, and storytelling through art—shaping not just his work, but his understanding of identity, connection, and the journey that defines him.
